Package views.session_load

Interface SessionLoadMainMenuViewBoundary

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MainMenuV
    public interface SessionLoadMainMenuViewBoundary
    A view boundary interface to open up the main menu and display a success message The MainMenuV view class implements this interface, and it is called by the SessionLoadMenuView class to switch over to the main menu after loading the session

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void openMainMenu​(java.lang.String message, SessionStorage session)
      Makes the main menu visible which displays the session data passed and displays a message in a popup

    • Method Detail

      • openMainMenu

        void openMainMenu​(java.lang.String message,
                  SessionStorage session)
        Makes the main menu visible which displays the session data passed and displays a message in a popup
        Parameters:
        message - a message to display in a popup after opening the menu
        session - the session data to display, or null if displaying a message is not needed
